List users             - cat /etc/passwd | cut -d: -f1
List groups            - cat /etc/group | cut -d: -f1
Create a new user      - sudo adduser newuser
Change user password of set password for the new user  -  sudo passwd username
Add new group          - sudo groupadd newgroup
Add existing user to group       - sudo usermod -a -G groupname username
Removing user from group         - sudo deluser username groupname
Change user primary group        - sudo usermod -g newgroup username
Delete a group                   - sudo groupdel groupname
Delete users                     - sudo deluser username
Add permissions                  - Chmod ugo+/- rwx filename
For view permission for a file   - Ls -l | grep file name
Add permissions via numbera      - Chmod 777 filename


To c programming

Touch filename.c  -> create file

Gcc filename.c -o temp -> compile (convert executable file)

./temp     -> execute 
